caption: Everything was delicious and fresh. Seasoned just right. I had the 6 piece southern chicken platter with collards and Mac and cheese. No complaints at all! I’m so satisfied and happy with my meal. Also the sweet potato pie was amazing, best I’ve had. Thank you

I had Mac and cheese, catfish strips, crab Balls, fried shrimp, fries, cornbread pie and sweet potato 🍠 pie. Everything was fire 🔥 They forgot my sweet potato pie at first. I drove back down there and they gave me a second pie. Plus while I was waiting on my whole order, I asked them could I eat my Mac and cheese and when everything was ready they gave me a second Mac and cheese. I showed them loved and they showed me big love back. I only treated myself to this delicious food cause it was my my birthday. I’ve lost 20 pounds in two months from cutting meat and dairy out of my diet by over 90% so shout-out to them from making my birthday meal the best birthday meal in my 30’s. I’m telling everyone about them. Somebody said their Mac and cheese was bland. Shiid not mine! If it wasn’t for me wanting to be civilized in the restaurant I would’ve screamed real loud about that Mac and cheese!

Ordered through Door Dash for delivery. I ordered 2 catfish platters. I am in a government building at work. I thought I only received 1 order of catfish with all the sides. So I called to let them know that I was missing and order of catfish but I have all the sides. I was put on hold for 5 mins for Joe to come back to the phone and say “Do you have 2 pieces of fish in the container”?. I answered yes. He stated and I quote “Well you have all of your food. Yah mein. So, we don’t have no delivery people here. So, it’s nothing I can do. I’m not the cook”. My response was you have a nice day. Never again. I don’t even know if the food is good. You put my food with a co-workers food. How exactly am I suppose to eat it with nothing to eat it on. I am too through!!!

While waiting I began eating and noticed my honey old bay wings were naked. I asked for a side of honey and old bay to pour it on myself. They were very nice and apologized. For that, I'd patronize again.

6:30 on a Friday night Next Phaze was a good place to be. Names to mention, Candy, Tony, Kim, Bre and Rico! With Candy's welcoming greeting, to Tony accomodating our party of 9, to Kim making sure we were taken care of until Bre got there to Rico keeping the the music going for the rest of the night, We had a ball!!! Bre was an excellent server. She kept everything flowing the whole night. Ms. Candy put her whole heart into every one of those cocktails. $6 Happy Hour drinks are worth every penny. You may even need an Uber if you drove. lol Food was excellent. The Caesar salad was delicious with the savory cornbread  croutons. The parmesan wings were so tender. We meet the chef, he hugged everyone at the table or I should say everyone at the table hugged him lol Rico the DJ was extra attentive to the Bday Queen we were there to celebrate. None of us had a complaint about anything. And just as Kim greeted us, she saw us all off to our cars. Thanks Next Phaze, we will be back

I’ve been a customer since they started having live music on Friday evenings.  I have not eaten there during the day.  On Friday evening the food is set up buffet style (the food selections are prepared in advance and dished out by servers).  Customers must stand in line to order from the menu of the day; and select an entree and two sides.  Their fried catfish is the hands down favorite.  The food preparation is very inconsistent; and 2 of 3 times I’ve been there I’ve returned either an entree or side dish. There isn’t any food or drink service.  Customers must get those items themselves.  On the other hand,  the music is jamming!!!  They’ve booked the top talent in the area; and that makes the visit to the the cafe worth my time.  What can I say?  I’m a music lover?
